data.title: Chaplain Awarded Bronze Star
data.meta_description: Father Stephen McDermott, a Philadelphia priest and U.S. Army chaplain, spent a year ministering to the service personnel and civilians in Afghanistan. data.text:
Father Stephen McDermott, a Philadelphia priest and U.S. Army chaplain, spent a year ministering to the service personnel and civilians in Afghanistan. The priest was recently awarded the Army’s Bronze Star Medal for his ministry.

Read the full article on CatholicPhilly.com

See pictures of Father McDermott from a gallery on CatholicPhilly.com
